
[1]episcopacy

   EPIS'COPACY, n. [L. episcopatus; Gr. to inspect, to see. See Bishop.]

   Government of the church by bishops; that form of ecclesiastical
   government, in which diocesan bishops are established, as distinct from
   and superior to priests or presbyters.
